SENATE BILL NO. 1798
103RD GENERA L ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY SENATOR TRENT.
7268S.01I KRISTINA MARTIN, Secretary
AN ACT
To repeal section 304.032, RSMo, and to enact in lieu thereof one new section relating to the
operation of utility vehicles, with penalty provisions.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Section 304.032, RSMo, is repealed and one new
2 section enacted in lieu thereof, to be known as section 304.032,
3 to read as follows:
1 304.032. 1. [No person shall operate a utility
2 vehicle, as defined in section 301.010, upon the highways of
3 this state, except as follows:
4 (1) Utility vehicles owned and operated by a
5 governmental entity for official use;
6 (2) Utility vehicles operated for agricultural
7 purposes or industrial on-premises purposes between the
8 official sunrise and sunset on the day of operation, unless
9 equipped with proper lighting;
10 (3) Utility vehicles operated by handicapped persons
11 for short distances occasionally only on the state's
12 secondary roads when operated between the hours of sunrise
13 and sunset;
14 (4) Governing bodies of cities may issue special
15 permits for utility vehicles to be used on highways within
16 the city limits by licensed drivers. Fees of fifteen
